    <body>
      <head>Emilie Schiff (née Strasser)</head>
      <div>

        <p>Daughter of Aron and Cäcilie Strasser, sister of <ref cRef="entity-008434">Charlotte
            (Lotti) Strasser [m. Fleischmann]</ref>, mother of <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette
            Schenker</ref>.</p>

        <p>Emilie Schiff was the wife of <ref cRef="entity-008431">Wilhelm (Wolf) Schiff</ref>, and
          mother of ten children: <list type="litany" rend="simple">

            <item><ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette [m. Kornfeld; m. Schenker]</ref>
              (1874–1945)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-006733">Louis</ref> (b 1875)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-008433">Emil</ref> (b. 1877)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-003245">Friedrika (Frieda) [m. Glässner]</ref>
              (1878–1933)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-006478">Emma [m. Winternitz]</ref> (1880–c.1943)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-003244">Klara [m. <ref cRef="entity-000339">Oskar
                Hatschek</ref>]</ref> (1881–1939)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-000944">Rosa (Růžena Rejle) [m. Weil]</ref> (1883–1942)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="[entity-000783]">Viktor (Victor)</ref></item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-003920">Helene (Hella) [m. <ref cRef="entity-008436">Emil
                  Hatschek</ref>]</ref> (1887–c.1941)</item>

            <item><ref cRef="entity-000782">Paul</ref> (b. 1895) (wife: <ref cRef="entity-000781"
                >Anna Schiff</ref>).</item>
          </list>
        </p>
      </div>
